Step one-
Create Employee class:
Name
Email Address
Age
Date Of Birth

(Start with a large amount of comma separated data stored in a text file)
(The data should visible in a form of a table)
(The first line of the file will always be a heading)
Operations:
    Add:
        Name
        Email Address
        Age
        Date Of Birth

        Pressing enter should create a record in the file and file should be updated.

    Delete:
        Ask for employee id
        Delete id from txt if it exist
        Else tell the user, id doesn't exist

    Search:
        Query(text to search)
        Sort(Order By)
        Direction(ascending or descending)

        Pressing enter should search based on the criteria and display the result on the console.

